What this is all about?
This is my graduation project "Accounting system of the professor's achievments on the JavaScript language"

More information soon ^^

1) To start local server use the following command:
npm run start

2) To start gulp without global installation, use the following command:
./node_modules/.bin/gulp script-name (in our case gulp_start)

3) If mongodb is not working, try the following command:
sudo service mongod start
   To check if it works type the following command:
sudo service mongod status

4) To undo a commit and redo use:
git commit -m "Misinfo"
git reset HEAD~
(edit files as necessary)
git add ...
git commit... again

5) To check all users in db type the following command:
db.users.find().pretty()

//////////////////////////////////////////////

--helpers - helper packages, such as Joi for data validation
--routes - routes
--config - configuration files

--bin/www - Server configuration
--app.js - app configuration (handlers for routes, middlewares, error handler, etc.)
--gulpfile.js - gulp, nodemon etc. configurations
--passport.js - passport configuration
